A hands-on Azure enterprise networking lab based on Microsoft best practices.

The lab includes:
- Hub-Spoke Virtual Network architecture
    - Created a resource group in Central India
    - Created a virtual network with address space 10.0.0.0/16
    - AzureBastionSubnet (required for Bastion)
    - AzureFirewallSubnet (For Firewall)
    - Default subnet for VM
    - Allowed SSH from Azure Bastion
    - Allowed HTTP traffic inside VNet
    - Denied all other inbound traffic
    - Deployed a Linux VM
    - No public IP assigned
- Azure Firewall
    - Created DNAT rules to access application via laptop browser
- Azure Bastion
    - Deployed Azure Bastion (Standard)
    - Used Bastion to securely connect to VM via browser
- User Defined Routes
- Secure VM access
    - Connected to VM via Azure Bastion
    - Installed Nginx web server
    - Started Nginx service
    - Verified application locall host and web browser.
